<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1169738071113">
<term>derivative function</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1169738071118">gives the derivative of a function at each point in the domain of the original function for which the derivative is defined</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1169738071124">
<term>differentiable at <emphasis effect="bold"><emphasis effect="italics">a</emphasis></emphasis></term>
<meaning id="fs-id1169738071129">a function for which <m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mi>f</m:mi><m:mo>′</m:mo></m:msup><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>a</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> exists is differentiable at <m:math><m:mi>a</m:mi></m:math></meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1169738071160">
<term>differentiable on <emphasis effect="bold"><emphasis effect="italics">S</emphasis></emphasis></term>
<meaning id="fs-id1169738071165">a function for which <m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mi>f</m:mi><m:mo>′</m:mo></m:msup><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> exists for each <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math> in the open set <m:math><m:mi>S</m:mi></m:math> is differentiable on <m:math><m:mi>S</m:mi></m:math></meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1169738071204">
<term>differentiable function</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1169738071210">a function for which <m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mi>f</m:mi><m:mo>′</m:mo></m:msup><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> exists is a differentiable function</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1169738071234">
<term>higher-order derivative</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1169738071240">a derivative of a derivative, from the second derivative to the <emphasis effect="italics">n</emphasis>th derivative, is called a higher-order derivative</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
